  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Joint Commemorative Stamps for India's Independence Celebration",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "On the occasion of India's 75th Independence Day celebrations, Sri Lanka and Indian Postal Departments have jointly decided to issue two commemorative stamps each.",
        "For this purpose, a proposal presented by the Minister of Transport, Highways and Mass Media, Dr. Bandula Gunawardena to sign a memorandum of understanding between the postal departments of the two countries has also been approved by the Cabinet.",
        "Cabinet Spokesman, Minister, Dr. Bandula Gunawardena said that it has been proposed to issue these commemorative stamps to reflect the parliaments of the two countries based on the theme of 'democracy'.",
        "The minister also mentioned that 3,000 sets of stamps, 5,000 souvenir sheets and 2,000 first-day covers each are expected to be exchanged from these stamps created by the two countries.",
        "The minister said this while addressing the press conference to inform the Cabinet decisions held today (16) at the Government Information Department."
      ],
